      "content": "that makes sense, i guess. but it still feels weird. it's like there's this hidden friction or something slowing everything down. is there any way to see the actual math? like if i have a 5% interest rate on a $30,000 balance, how exactly do they figure out what my interest charge is for the first month? i just want to see the raw numbers so i can understand where the money is going.",
